In a large skillet, brown beef and pork over medium heat until no longer pink; set aside. In a large skillet, warm olive oil over medium heat and saute onions and garlic until tender; add about 1/2 cup of wine; mix well. Add mushrooms, rosemary, oregano and thyme to skillet and add another 1/2 cup wine; saute until tender. Add browned meat, tomato sauce and tomato paste to mixture; simmer for 1 hour and add the remaining 2 cups of wine. Simmer sauce on low for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally; serve.